                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6838: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Legation in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-26T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 26, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 26—8:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. A report from apparently reliable unofficial source states that on January 23
                    the Minister of Foreign Affairs informed a meeting of the Central Political
                    Council that he had received a telegram direct <pb facs="0133" n="21"
                        xml:id="pg_21"/> from the Japanese Minister for Foreign Affairs announcing
                    the desire of the latter to visit Nanking; also the Japanese Minister to China
                    in a recent interview proposed an offensive and defensive alliance between China
                    and Japan. The meeting decided to study both matters. I am endeavoring to
                    confirm this report.</p>
                <p>2. Report that an alliance had been proposed as stated was first given me by the
                    French Minister on January 5 who received it in Shanghai. Our subsequent
                    investigations led us to regard it as unreliable but this independent
                    confirmation lends some credibility. I will continue attempts at
                    verification.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
